---
import Document from '../../layouts/Document.astro';
import Annot from '../../components/Annot.astro';
import AnnotLine from '../../components/AnnotLine.astro';
import CId from '../../components/CId.astro';
import ClaimRef from '../../components/ClaimRef.astro';
import CountUp from '../../components/CountUp.astro';
import { getClaim } from '../../lib/data';
import { exactUsd } from '../../lib/format';

const paidOut = exactUsd(getClaim('C-0001'));   // $7,009,973,667,049
const awards = exactUsd(getClaim('C-0005'));     // $5,299,254,815,599
const residual = exactUsd(getClaim('C-0026'));   // $1,710,718,851,450
const unreported = exactUsd(getClaim('C-0009')); // $206,921,871,135
---

<Document title="THE BLACK LEDGER — 02 The Reconciliation">
  <section class="section section--first">
    <p class="chapter-title">The reconciliation.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Ledger block 1: the subtraction (spec §5, §7.6) -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="scroll-x">
      <div class="lrow">
        <span class="lrow__label">WHAT THE TREASURY PAID OUT, FY2025</span>
        <span class="lrow__amount">{paidOut}</span>
      </div>
      <Annot>
        <AnnotLine key="Source">Monthly Treasury Statement, Table 5 · Total Outlays</AnnotLine>
        <ClaimRef id="C-0001" />
      </Annot>

      <div class="lrow">
        <span class="lrow__label">WHAT IS TRACEABLE AS AWARDS</span>
        <span class="lrow__amount">− {awards}</span>
      </div>
      <Annot>
        <AnnotLine key="Source">USAspending · all award types, FY2025</AnnotLine>
        <ClaimRef id="C-0005" />
        <AnnotLine key="Basis note">outlays and obligations differ; treatment in Chapter 05.2</AnnotLine>
      </Annot>

      <div class="lrow lrow--total">
        <span class="lrow__label">THE RESIDUAL</span>
        <span class="lrow__amount">{residual}</span>
      </div>
      <Annot>
        <AnnotLine key="Computation">C-0001 − C-0005</AnnotLine>
        <AnnotLine>Ledger: <CId id="C-0026" /></AnnotLine>
        <AnnotLine key="Composition">debt interest, federal compensation, non-award operations — and everything else</AnnotLine>
      </Annot>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="body">Most of the residual is explainable, and this document explains it before drawing any conclusion from it. What the residual establishes is simpler: the disclosed classified budget — $101.1 billion — is not a separate universe. It sits inside ordinary Treasury arithmetic, alongside a second figure the government prints itself.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Ledger block 2: the unreported line -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="scroll-x">
      <div class="lrow">
        <span class="lrow__label">THE SYSTEM'S OWN LINE FOR WHAT IT ISN'T TOLD</span>
        <span class="lrow__amount">{unreported}</span>
      </div>
      <Annot>
        <AnnotLine key="Label in source">"Unreported Data" · USAspending Spending Explorer, FY2025</AnnotLine>
        <ClaimRef id="C-0009" />
        <AnnotLine key="Prior year">$164.4 bn (<CId id="C-0010" />) · change: +$42.5 bn · +25.9%</AnnotLine>
        <AnnotLine key="Note">includes, but is not limited to, classified activity</AnnotLine>
      </Annot>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison statement — the thesis ratio (spec §5). One accent per viewport (§9): 2.9% -->
  <section class="section">
    <p class="compare"><CountUp value={2.9} decimals={1} suffix="%" signal={true} /> of everything the Treasury paid out is unreported to the government's own tracking system.</p>
    <p class="compare"><CountUp value={1.4} decimals={1} suffix="%" /> is acknowledged as classified.</p>
    <Annot>
      <AnnotLine key="Computation">$206.9 bn ÷ $7.010 tn · $101.1 bn ÷ $7.010 tn</AnnotLine>
      <AnnotLine>The first figure is the one that grew 26% in a year.</AnnotLine>
    </Annot>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="body">No other public resource performs this subtraction. USAspending prints the unreported line but does not total it against the Treasury. The Treasury publishes the total but does not decompose it. The sites that explain federal spending in plain language exclude classified expenditure entirely, and say so in a footnote. This chapter is that footnote, given a ledger of its own.</p>
  </section>
</Document>
